column93: Quite a few experiments, assumed some values for several (i.e. 600C annealing for thickness study)
column94: spin-coating 4000 rpm 20 s. It is a randomly oriented polycrystalline film for the BFO films grown on Pt/Ti/SiO2/Si and Si substrates, while a highly (00l)-preferred crystalline orientation for the BFO film grown on LNO/Si. This may be attributed to the fact that the LNO sol tends to form a stable perovskite phase crystal structure on Si substrate and LNO has a good in-plane lattice match with Si ([110]LNO//[100]Si), thus the grains will be easily grown along the lowest free energy plane of (00l), eventually leading to an excellent (00l)-preferred orientation in LNO film layer

This may be attributed to the fact that the LNO sol tends to form a stable perovskite phase crystal structure on Si substrate and LNO has a good in-plane lattice match with Si ([110]LNO//[100]Si), thus the grains will be easily grown along the lowest free energy plane of (00l), eventually leading to an excellent (00l)-preferred orientation in LNO film layer
